  "summary": "Main\nBy Jeffrey Landsberg\nChinese banks issued 2.47 trillion yuan in new loans in September. This marks a month-on-month increase of 1.22 trillion yuan (98%) and a year-on-year increase of 810 billion yuan (49%). China's new loans have each now increased on both a month-on-month and year-on-year basis during four of the last five months.",
